programme.title: Silk Railroad E1
programme.desc: The Belt and Road Initiative is connecting China to Europe in a bid to boost trade connections with the west. Yiwu, an inland city 300km from Shanghai, is a terminus on this east-west trade network which has been dubbed the new Silk Railroad. One of the wealthiest cities in China, Yiwu made its riches through the sale of knick- knacks. In 2016 alone, it exported exporting over $25.6 billion worth of goods. With this new transportation network that transports goods to Europe in 16 days as compared to one year via the ancient silk road, historian Sam Willis and ChInese journalist Li Qiuyuan want to explore how this new railway is rehashing Yiwu's trading heritage and how it's changing how Yiwu trades with the west.

programme.title: Silk Railroad E2
programme.desc: 2000 years ago, in the time of the ancient Silk Road, the journey between China, Central Asia and Europe often took an entire year. Today, goods can be transported overland in just 14 days thanks to the world's longest rail service, a 13,000 KM route that connects China and Europe. Now, with ancient connections being revived for the 21st century, historian Sam Willis and journalist Li Qiuyuan travel to Chengdu, to explore how a new era of trade is shaping the city.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E13
programme.sub-title: Seven Wonders Of The New World
programme.desc: The young Carl Sagan and Neil Tyson first discovered their passion for science at the NY World's Fairs of the past. We visit the dazzling Pavilions of the 2039 NY World's Fair, where problems we currently think intractable have been plausibly solved through public commitment and scientific imagination. And our baby is a woman now, with a baby of her own and a future bright with possibilities.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E14
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Japanese Empire rose to power in the Pacific and how it harnessed superior technology turning that devastating firepower against the Allies. It reveals hidden secrets of a catastrophic attack on Australia that gave Japan control of the region and how its extraordinary tactics brought the British Empire to its knees.

programme.title: Paris To Pittsburgh
programme.desc: Paris to Pittsburgh brings to life the impassioned efforts of individuals who are battling the most severe threats of climate change in their own backyards. Set against the national debate over the United States' energy future - and the Trump administration's explosive decision to exit the Paris Climate Agreement - the film captures what's at stake for communities around the country and the inspiring ways Americans are responding.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E20
programme.desc: In this episode we learn about motorcycle flips, how to avoid hurt when attempting to parkour lache, and how to avoid humiliation when walking up stairs.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E12
programme.desc: On this episode, officers profile a man carrying 20 alpaca skin rugs, who claims that they are souvenirs when they really contain hidden narcotics inside. In another operation, officers inspect the luggage of a young student carrying narcotics in a double-bottom suitcase; they interrogate a hostile passenger who refuses to cooperate with the police; and later on, they spot a suspicious young man carrying almost 3 kilograms of cocaine hidden in his luggage.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E6
programme.desc: On an adventure through Central America, Tom Hart Dyke and Paul Winder are kidnapped and have a $3 million price tag placed on their heads. Nine months and no money later, the pair is released into the jungle but after a couple of days roaming, they get lost. They reluctantly decide to return to their captors for proper directions, although they are warned if they do, their heads will roll.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S2E4
programme.desc: It is story of journey, travelled by tribal children from interiors of Odisha to a national level and the world stage. It is a world's largest tribal school. This is also an inspiring & uplifting human story about empowering the poorest of the poor. Feeding their dreams with education and a full plate...is the Kalinga institute of social sciences. Presenting the MEGA facts of the kitchen, 25,000 children are fed 3 meals a day (approx. 76000 in total) in a 10,000-capacity dining hall on an 80 acre campus.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E4
programme.desc: Piers Gibbon travels to Cameroon to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional Cameroonian medicine. Joining Piers are anxiety sufferer Jenna Patel and Dwight Werner, who has arthritis, back pain and sleep apnea, as they experience a range of extreme treatments. They are on a mission to find a potential cure that Western medicine has been unable to provide.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E4
programme.desc: The newest member of the community, Amanda's story illustrates how the Lawless Island community welcomes newcomers and guides them into self-sustaining Alaskans.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E5
programme.desc: China has built some of the most impressive structures that have lasted the test of time, such as the Forbidden City and the Great Wall of China. But as the nation modernizes, so do its architectural needs and aspirations. Historian Sam Willis explores the history of Chinese architecture, the innovations and cultural considerations involved, and how it has evolved for the growing cities and future generations.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E8
programme.desc: Woodsman Thorn takes Delia on her very first hunt to capture a bird to in an attempt to meld together the wild and domestic sides of his life, homesteaders Tony and Amelia struggle to maintain unruly and destructive pigs, hunter-gatherer Matt invites old friends over for a turkey roast, and frontiersman Colbert enlists the help of two friends to help him finish his cabin in time for spring.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S9E1
programme.desc: As the season opens, Gloucester's elite get challenged by top new fishermen. Captain Bob Cook and his crew on Fat Tuna vow to dethrone reigning champion Dave Carraro on FV-Tuna.Com. Tyler on Pinwheel faces off with Krakens captain Sam Law who is out to settle a personal score, while Hot Tuna is the target of Wasabi co-captains Zack Plante and Charlie Boivin who believe they've got more grit than TJ Ott. The new contenders arrival tests the Gloucester fleet in ways they've never faced before as a heated battle for bluefin begins on the Atlantic Ocean.

programme.title: Mega Icons E4
programme.desc: Kiran Bedi, (born June 9, 1949, Amritsar, India), the first woman to join the Indian Police Service (IPS) and a social activist who was instrumental in introducing prison reform in India. Bedi was the second of four daughters. Her education included an undergraduate degree in English (1968), a master's degree in political science (1970), a law degree (1988), and a Ph.D. in social science (1993) with a focus on drug abuse and domestic violence. She joined the IPS in 1972 and went on to serve a variety of roles, including narcotics officer, antiterrorist specialist, and administrator. Bedi earned recognition for the work she did as inspector general of prisons, beginning in 1994. In that capacity she reshaped one of the largest prisons in the world-the Tihar prison complex, in Delhi-by addressing the corruption and human rights abuses she found there. She targeted sanitation and nutrition problems at Tihar and also implemented new literacy and drug treatment programs there. In.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E4
programme.desc: Oil worker Steve has owned his Aston Martin DB6 for over 20 years. After buying it for a bargain price the car became his pride and joy but when it broke down his attempts to repair the Aston failed. Since then a serious fall and chronic health problems have taken their toll and restoring the British classic is now out of his reach. While Fuzz struggles with an engine that hasn't turned over in 20 years Tim will have to do his best to get all the right Aston parts which are notoriously expensive.

programme.title: Genius S2E2
programme.desc: WWII rages, but older Picasso (Antonio Banderas) refuses to leave Paris, straining his relationship with photographer Dora Maar (Samantha Colley). Meanwhile, Young Pablo (Alex Rich) finds quick success on his first trip to Paris by imitating the masters, but he struggles to make something truly original.

programme.title: One Strange Rock E1
programme.desc: For the privileged few who have looked down at the Earth from space, the thin blue line of our planet's sets the Earth apart from every other planet we've seen. It sustains life. The story of how the Earth creates and regulates that oxygen rich-atmosphere is mind-blowing: A flying river, a global dust storm, a collapsing glacier and the most important creature you've never heard of. All connected together to allow life and the planet to breathe.

programme.title: New Orleans: City Of Stories
programme.desc: Delving into the history and culture of the Big Easy. This special showcases some of the best when local storytellers reveal the secrets of what unfolds behind its courtyard walls and ornate facades.

programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz have taken on a legendary 1980s French hot hatch, the mighty Renault 5 GT Turbo. Can Tim and Fuzz get his dream car back on the road?

programme.desc: Historian Sam Willis embarks on a journey through China to uncover how an ancient people crafted their world. Discover the pivotal role China's crafts played in the development of a unique identity that influenced the course of world history.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E7
programme.desc: A suspicious solo passenger arriving into LAX from Nigeria tells a story that doesn't quite add up. And HSI agents at JFK have their hands full with a controlled delivery of MDMA, plus multiple food couriers suspected of importing more than just snacks within checked luggage.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E11
programme.desc: The Outer Banks Bluefin quota is filling up fast and with the legal limit for catching them at one fish a day, the competition is getting fierce. Northern and Southern fleets are determined to do whatever it takes to get paydays for their crews but when one captain loses his mate, a dangerous game ensues. Only the strong survive but who has what it takes in the battle between man and nature?

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E2
programme.desc: The Jungles of southern Yunnan are unique in China. Home to its greatest diversity of life. From primates to bears, fishing bats to bees and elephants to caterpillars, this is their story. With abundant resources life here should be easy but to survive, each must find its way to thrive. The creatures here have done exactly that through amazing adaptations some of which are filmed for the very first time.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E6
programme.desc: For forty years, Nimitz class aircraft carriers have delivered US military might wherever it is needed, anywhere on the globe. But now, this legendary design is being phased out and new carriers are planned. But until they're ready, the giant Nimitz ships have to be kept at the forefront of military technology. In this episode, engineer and host Chad Zdenek spends a week on board the USS Carl Vinson to work with the highly trained specialist engineers, mechanics and sailors who keep this incredible floating city in perfect working order during a critical mission in the Pacific - training twenty F18 pilots who have never taken off from an Aircraft Carrier before. This gives Chad the chance to discover the five engineering innovations at the heart of America's most incredible Aircraft Carrier.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E13
programme.desc: Jordan checks out the bay area's biggest city, Oakland, California, long known for its tremendous diversity and thriving arts and entertainment scene, and amazing Asian cuisine. His first stop is Seawolf Public House in Jack London Square, a new local where Chef Jason Moniz mashes up classic pub food with international flavours.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E1
programme.desc: Jordan checks out Toronto, Canada's most diverse city, it dishes out all kinds of delights. He kicks off his tour at Chanticler, a French style bistro located in Parkdale, an artsy enclave with a hopping late vibe.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E3
programme.desc: At the start of week three of the bluefin tuna season, every boat in the fleet has caught fish except for Hard Merchandise. Desperate to provide for his family, the pressure weighs heavily on Marciano's shoulders to land his first tuna and bring home a paycheck. Meanwhile, as Pinwheel fights to maintain the lead, second place Hot Tuna's Captain TJ Ott counts on his 10-year-old nephew, Danny, to bring luck to Hot Tuna and push them to the top.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E8
programme.desc: On its final approach to Zurich, Alitalia Flight 404 plows into a forested hillside killing everyone on board. Checking the DC-9's radar track, Swiss investigators immediately notice the aircraft was flying too low. But closer analysis of the evidence only deepens the mystery. Did a hidden flaw in the navigation system lead two pilots down a deadly path?

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S14E3
programme.desc: On October 4, 1992, El Al Flight 1862 Boeing 747-258F cargo jet with a heavy load of cargo loses control just minutes from the airport, rolling hard to the right and flying into an 11-storey apartment complex despite the pilots managing to turn the crippled aircraft around. Investigators discover a potentially lethal problem with every 747 in the sky.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S4E2
programme.desc: With a smoke-filled cabin and malfunctioned engines, will British Airways Flight 9 get to land in Perth, Australia on the fateful day of 24 June 1982?

programme.title: One Strange Rock E2
programme.desc: Ever wondered how our planet got here? It was born in a cosmic storm and shaped by violence. We're only here because of random collisions in a dangerous cosmos. It could have destroyed us, but instead constructed a planet from the rubble of the early solar system, gave us oceans in a bombardment from the heavens, and brought order to our world when two planets collided.

programme.title: Living Free With Kimi Werner E1
programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.title: Inside The Ring
programme.desc: Inside the Ring is the extraordinary tale of how racers' quest for speed gave rise to a world famous grand prix circuit, the Nurburgring, and how it found new life as the ultimate automotive testing venue. With unprecedented access, we uncover what happens behind the latest top-secret facilities, and follow the development behind N division's new cutting-edge high-performance machine.

programme.title: Miracle Hospital S2E1
programme.desc: Merrily and her unborn baby could die if doctors can't navigate round a massive fibroid in her womb without causing catastrophic bleeding. University student Sam's rare tumours are causing life-threatening pressure in his brain. Using critical technology two surgeons conduct a marathon 8-hour operation to remove the largest tumour. Helen's spinal surgery requires millimeter precision if doctors are to cure her excruciating neck pain.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S9E1
programme.desc: As the season opens, Gloucester's elite get challenged by top new fishermen. Captain Bob Cook and his crew on Fat Tuna vow to dethrone reigning champion Dave Carraro on FV-Tuna.Com. Tyler on Pinwheel faces off with Krakens captain Sam Law who is out to settle a personal score, while Hot Tuna is the target of Wasabi co-captains Zack Plante and Charlie Boivin who believe they've got more grit than TJ Ott. The new contenders arrival tests the Gloucester fleet in ways they've never faced before as a heated battle for bluefin begins on the Atlantic Ocean.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E10
programme.desc: En route to Boise, Idaho, Continental Airlines Flight 1713 is delayed on the tarmac in Denver where controllers struggle to keep departures on schedule amid heavy snow. When the plane is finally cleared for take-off, the DC-9 barely lifts off the ground before its banks sharply and crashes. Investigators find nothing wrong with the aircraft itself, but what they eventually uncover changes commercial flight forever.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E3
programme.desc: The colonial history of Sri Lanka is seen through its iconic colonial bungalows. The imprint of the Europeans on Ceylon was most evident with the spectacular Walauwas built for the powerful class that formed the bridge between the colonial administration and the locals. The fusion of European and local Sri Lankan architecture produced extraordinarily unique tropical mansions.

programme.title: Warrior Road Trip E3
programme.desc: Boni and Lemarti are two Kenyan warriors from the Maasai and neighbouring Samburu tribe. They have been best friends since they met during warrior training when they were teenagers. But Boni and Lemarti are no ordinary Maasai. They listen to hip-hop, ride motorcycles and speak three languages. Yet it's their roots as blood-drinking warriors that define them. On their journey Boni and Lemarti share their way of life with everyone they meet, enjoying the cultural exchange of ideas and showing us 'the way of the warrior'. Their simple, naturalistic approach to life collides with the fast paced mass-consumerist society of the West. As Boni and Lemarti struggle to get their heads around western culture, we reflect on our own choices and what we take for granted. Through the eyes of these ultimate outsiders, we see we are stranger than we think.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E11
programme.desc: Walking tours are all the rage in major metropolitan cities, and Durban is no different. Beset Durban is a free tour group operated by three young professionals, who take David on a private trek through their beloved city. They give David a crash course on some of the city's history, and check out some of the best local hotspots for delicious food. Through them, we learn about a city rich in culture and history, built on the backs of Indian immigrants, which is now currently experiencing an economic and social revitalization that you can feel on every street corner and with every food vendor.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E12
programme.desc: Lalibela Ethiopia, seems at first glance like a town lost to time, but with a closer look you can see that the economy is booming and the population is experiencing huge growth which is creating hope for a bright new future. David spends time with some of the locals to get their perspective on this bright future, while he learns how to make a few Ethiopian staples like Shiro, Injera and Berbere, the traditional Ethiopian spice mix that's a must in so many dishes.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E13
programme.desc: Nestled in the northern foothills of Ethiopia is the remote small town of Lalibela. It's considered one of the holiest places in the world, especially during the all-important Easter week celebrations. David takes in all the rituals and traditions, which date back over 1000 years, as he visits the beautiful monolithic churches, carved directly into the stone. A big part of Easter for the orthodox people of Lalibela is the 'breaking of the fast' after a 55 day period of Lent. David helps prepare for the traditional feast, with a visit to the huge Easter market, the slaughter, and finally, the preparations of the delicious meal which the entire family comes out to enjoy.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E1
programme.desc: Jordan's in Memphis, a city known for BBQ and the Blues, but there's much more to its late night food scene. Jordan's firing up the evening with some Polynesian fare gone Southern at Atomic Tiki, a hidden tropical oasis in Overton Park. He whets his appetite with some pork belly steamed buns and gets a glimpse of their top selling favourite, the Polynesian meatballs before heading downtown.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E8
programme.desc: Fourteen Tanks. Twenty-seven reefs. One project. The South Florida Science Museum draws hundreds of thousands of visitors and they're building a new aquarium wing. The challenges are endless, from planning the displays, to constructing a shipwreck and balancing the different ecosystems perfectly, Living Colors next project is by far the most extensive yet.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S2E4
programme.desc: The Costa Deliziosa is heading for the Arctic Circle. Europe has been rocked by an outbreak of E-coli and a new Hotel Director has been brought on to enforce a sanitation programme. Australian Paul Huisintveld must settle in quickly as well as train a new Russian hostess. Franco, a dining room waiter with dreams of stardom, has been given permission to go all out in a dance routine.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E7
programme.desc: Ben arrives at one of his favourite community organisations, Produce to the People, on Tasmania's North-West Coast. He chats to Penelope, the founder of PTTP, and collects some fresh produce from around the farm to use in a recipe. He makes his version of lox and cream with a slight twist and some added pickled vegetables. Dr Mark Turner explains why pickling will preserve your fruit and vegetables.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E8
programme.desc: Ben prepares an Asian Chilli Chicken with the ingredients he found in Frankie the Food Truck and fresh produce from around the farm. While Ben's dish is simmering away, he has a quick chat with Penelope, the founder of PTTP, and discusses the importance of the organisation within the community. Next Ben makes a simple and healthy tartare, with a slight twist to the traditional.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E9
programme.desc: Ben arrives at the Pelican Point Sanctuary, down the East Coast of Tasmania. He sets up for a cook next to a beautiful stretch of water and prepares a fresh Salmon Tartare, paired with a vibrant, crisp salad. Next Ben makes a Raspberry Honeycomb, while Joel discusses what chemical reactions are taking place.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E5
programme.desc: Ariana travels to Tabriz, the birthplace of her father, who inspired her to be a chef. She visits some historic sites including the Grand Bazaar and Khaneh Mashrouteh where she meets a woman who runs a restaurant and is an example of the modern entrepreneurial Iranian woman. She also gets to satisfy her sweet tooth with qurabiya, a kind of almond macaroon that originates in Tabriz.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E4
programme.desc: Geoffrey Bawa's fusion of colonial and local Sri Lankan architecture birthed Tropical Modernism and is indicative of a new independent Sri Lanka. Witness his clever use of light and space in a stable turned into a weekend home. Following in his mentor's footsteps, his apprentice, now a successful architect himself, built a home which pays homage to the past but looks to the future at the same time.

programme.title: Jose Andres: Dinner In Haiti
programme.desc: Join world-renowned chef Jose Andres on an exploration of Haiti, the most unknown country in the Caribbean. Along the way Andres experiences the authentic Haiti's traditions and rituals, from making cassava bread to midnight gatherings with vodou priests, and through its unique cuisine he discovers the history and culture, and sees into the future, of a proud and rarely understood people.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E5
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the Island of Maui, Hawaii, to explore the secrets of Hawaiian cuisine along the rugged Hana coastline.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E9
programme.desc: Fabio Lisboa, a lifelong fish enthusiast, is looking to make his dreams come true. His vision is a 5000-gallon tank full of sharks. An aquarium that size will not only take up over half of his office, but will be the largest private tank in South Florida. As always, Living Color is up to the challenge.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E2
programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. He's there to learn the secret behind their mouthwatering fried chicken, which some say is the best in the south. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E2
programme.desc: Clint flies in by sea plane to view the Grizzly Bears up close and also gets his hands dirty at Echo Valley Ranch in British Columbia.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E4
programme.desc: For a lot of people, Tawang is synonymous with Buddhism. The ginormous Himalayas, a magnificent monastery, small houses with yellow tops and lamas in red robes makes Tawang very picturesque. Meeting and eating with the monks, paying regards at a centuries-old stupa of Zimithang, and cooking some favorite foods of the Nun are what Pablo's journey to Tawang all about.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E5
programme.desc: A beautiful laid back village in the remote areas of Ukhrul district of Manipur, Pablo landed here to meet the Thangkul Tribe. Welcomed by the very gentle king of the Thangkuls, Pablo shares his experience of having cockroaches and jungle squirrel for lunch. Later, he was invited over for a meal by someone who is not just an amazing cook but a very famous musician.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E6
programme.desc: One of the most iconic things in Darjeeling apart from the tea gardens is the toy train. After the train expedition Pablo met his host, with whom he enjoyed English breakfast at a place that was straight out of the British Era. Next stop is definitely the tea estate where he was enlightened by the tea master and Mrs. Chettri later invited Pablo to enjoy a very important dish- Gundruk.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E8
programme.desc: Beneath the ancient castles and cathedrals of Prague is a hidden underworld that traces the story of this World Heritage through the ages. But time and the forces of nature are threatening to destroy what's survived for over a thousand years. Now, teams of explorers, engineers and master craftsmen must go inside Prague's secret spaces to safeguard its cherished heritage.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E3
programme.desc: First time property developer Cate and her fiancee Nikki are looking to boost their pension pot and they carry out a high risk strategy by pouring all of Cate's life savings into a rundown house they don't even own. Will her dream of making a £200,000 profit turn into a nightmare?

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E5
programme.desc: Clarke has a good look at one of the most productive harbours in New Zealand. Home to over 20% of the world's seabird biodiversity and with a resident whale population, this unique location is an incredible harbinger of life. Clarke explores some of the harbours hidden features and shows a fishing club that has made big changes to better utilize the ocean around it.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E6
programme.desc: Chasing a Dog Tooth Tuna, Clarke encounters everything but as he tackles the waters off Apia Island, Samoa. Not that he has any complaints as he manages to hook the largest Giant Trevally he has ever captured. He also gets in the water to discover that Samoa has some incredible spearfishing in the warm clear tropical waters that surround it.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E4
programme.desc: The taste of Chinese medicinal herbs, bitter flavor is said to clear 'heat', strengthen the stomach, and promote salivation. Bitterness in often found in Chinese cooking, but rarely used alone. Christine cooks a popular local bitter ingredient, and makes a less than delicious visit to a Traditional Chinese Medicine shop, experiencing firsthand the power of bitter herbs.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E3
programme.desc: The home of the nation's most inventive small spaces continues as George travels to Lancashire to meet Billy, a remarkable 17 year old self-builder who singlehandedly transforms a derelict narrow boat his mum bought for £4000 into a hand crafted floating holiday home for his mum and sister, and the results are amazing.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E20
programme.desc: Pablo's belief that magic happens in the most unexpected places was just reaffirmed after this trip to the North East of India. programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E19
programme.desc: Food has always been a way to spread joy and happiness for Pablo. When he got a chance to return the favour, Pablo couldn't think of a better way than to cook for the people of North East and share the magic of food with them. Pablo talks about his most innovative dishes given the limited amount of time and unusual ingredients, he churned out some amazing recipes in the North East of India.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E4
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the remote corners of New Zealand's South Island on an adventure to discover the secrets of Maori cuisine.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E4
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the remote corners of New Zealand's South Island on an adventure to discover the secrets of Maori cuisine.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E9
programme.desc: In Northern Kenya's unforgiving desert landscape, Lake Turkana's shores are home to the oldest-known fossil remains of our human ancestors. Over the years, Turkana's already parched land has faced an environmental catastrophe – the Lake is drying up. Scientists and experts have been relentless in their quest to protect this remarkable land for the sake of understanding our human story.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E4
programme.desc: Two developers, worlds apart, but with one thing in common – they seem to have bitten off more than they can chew. In Wales, Rebecca, a 26-year-old University Lecturer has a get rich quick scheme to save her from Generation Rent. In Croydon, Jas is juggling a new baby with a large Victorian house that he wants to convert into 3 flats.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E7
programme.desc: Clarke continues his adventure in Samoa. Hunting an elusive Dog Tooth tuna for Chef John, he encounters many other fish along the way including a huge Blue Marlin. He also has a chance to explore more the Island discovering a huge secret family cave with an incredible history many hundreds of years old.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E8
programme.desc: Clarke heads off on a South Island, NZ driving adventure. See him learning more about New Zealand's indigenous Dolphin population and the threat it faces. He also explores local waterways learning about the importance of clean local water ways to Maori before tackling wild Salmon in South Island's famous canals.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E13
programme.desc: After spending some time in the crazy crowds of Old Delhi, David decides to head for the greener pastures of ITC Grand Bharat, a golf resort and a peaceful oasis just outside the city. There, he plays a few holes with the help of a pro and a knowledgeable caddie, and cooks up a storm on the outdoor grill with resident Chef Shiveet.

programme.title: Tom's Istanbul Delight E4
programme.desc: Tom explores Istanbul’s love affair with cooking over fire. He begins his adventure in the smoky heart of the city, Taksim, and samples the fiery flavors and charcoal grills. Next he learns what tea means to Turkish people, both culturally and gastronomically. Finally, after tasting a chicken dessert, Tom returns to his kitchen and makes his take on Lahmacun, known to the world as Turkish pizza.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E4
programme.desc: George travels to West Sussex to meet young couple Becky and Joe, who plan to build their first home together, a tiny house, on the back of an old trailer to enable them to live independently, debt-free.

programme.title: The Longest Hole: Golfing Across Mongolia
programme.desc: Set against the backdrop of one of the most incredible and diverse wildernesses on the planet, Adam Rolston and Ron Rutland set out to play the world's longest hole of golf ever played, trekking 2011km's over 80 days, unsupported across Mongolia, playing within the Rules and the Spirit of the game.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E20
programme.desc: Pablo's belief that magic happens in the most unexpected places was just reaffirmed after this trip to the North East of India. Discovering ingredients and flavors that he had never heard of, never tasted or never even imagined existed came into his way. To add to all of this, the wonderful people of North East left no stone unturned to open their hearts and kitchens for Pablo.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E9
programme.desc: In Northern Kenya's unforgiving desert landscape, Lake Turkana's shores are home to the oldest-known fossil remains of our human ancestors. Over the years, Turkana's already parched land has faced an environmental catastrophe – the Lake is drying up. Scientists and experts have been relentless in their quest to protect this remarkable land for the sake of understanding our human story.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E4
programme.desc: Two developers, worlds apart, but with one thing in common – they seem to have bitten off more than they can chew. In Wales, Rebecca, a 26-year-old University Lecturer has a get rich quick scheme to save her from Generation Rent. In Croydon, Jas is juggling a new baby with a large Victorian house that he wants to convert into 3 flats.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E7
programme.desc: Clarke continues his adventure in Samoa. Hunting an elusive Dog Tooth tuna for Chef John, he encounters many other fish along the way including a huge Blue Marlin. He also has a chance to explore more the Island discovering a huge secret family cave with an incredible history many hundreds of years old.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E8
programme.desc: Clarke heads off on a South Island, NZ driving adventure. See him learning more about New Zealand's indigenous Dolphin population and the threat it faces. He also explores local waterways learning about the importance of clean local water ways to Maori before tackling wild Salmon in South Island's famous canals.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E5
programme.desc: Despite popular belief ‘spicy' in Chinese cuisines is not always hot! In various Chinese cuisines, spices are complex and varied. Chef Christine visits the Malaysian island of Penang, a location historically important to the story of spice trade with TV celebrity Chef Wan for a fun and fact filled visit to the Tropical Spice Garden.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E4
programme.desc: George travels to West Sussex to meet young couple Becky and Joe, who plan to build their first home together, a tiny house, on the back of an old trailer to enable them to live independently, debt-free.

programme.title: Shandong: Land of Confucius
programme.desc: Shandong Province is home to China's most famous philosopher- Confucius, Jonathan Clements as a historian and expert on Asian Culture, will be the host of this show. In the course of a whirlwind adventure that spans 9 carefully chosen locations throughout Shandong, Clements, a scholar of modern Asian trends gives us his fascinating take on how China got where it is today.

programme.title: Don't Tell My Mother S3E9
programme.desc: Diego explores where past and present collide in the biggest city in the world, Tokyo. Japan is one of the most technologically-advanced places on the planet, and in the richest city in Asia, the line between reality and fiction seems thin. From the wild to the traditional, the classic to the outlandish, discover Tokyo like you’ve never seen it before.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E20
programme.desc: Pablo's belief that magic happens in the most unexpected places was just reaffirmed after this trip to the North East of India. Discovering ingredients and flavors that he had never heard of, never tasted or never even imagined existed came into his way. To add to all of this, the wonderful people of North East left no stone unturned to open their hearts and kitchens for Pablo.

programme.title: Island Hunter E3
programme.desc: Easy island vibes, lots of amazing local rum, brilliant natural landscapes and those amazing beaches! Of course, Island Hunter is in Jamaica! But in this episode, host Liesel Hlista shows you a different side of the Irie nation; away from the hordes of people unleashed via cruise liners! She starts off with a quick glimpse and an impromptu jam session at the birthplace of Bob Marley, Trench town, noshes on the most delicious ice cream this side of the hemisphere, and plunges into Mystic mountain's waterfalls. Jamaica is known for being the home of the all-inclusive resort and Liesel finds out exactly why that is - with stays at Ian Fleming inspired Golden eye Hotel as well as Sunset at the Palms! Lazy tubing down the river, limestone foot massages, topped up with historic food tours and experiencing local cuisines such as jerk chicken and the amazing seafood; this is Jamaica, Island Hunter style!

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E4
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets the little known Lisu ethnic minority and gets himself into Lisu courtship and wedding but also learns about manly activities like making crossbows, playing musical instruments and climbing a ladder of upturned knives.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E5
programme.desc: Although Manu has visited Tokyo before, this time he is on his own and has a tight budget. Still, he is keen to learn and discover as much as he can. His first stop is the legendary fish market to learn about the renowned tuna sold there but he has to make it through the craziness of the Tokyo fish market first.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E6
programme.desc: Los Angeles is not only the center of the world's biggest film and television industry, it is also the leader in setting trends. For many years now LA has been on a health kick, making it relatively easy for people to live a healthier lifestyle. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E3
programme.desc: As a lifelong lover of Chinese food, when John Torode's tour of Asian cuisine stops off in Beijing, he is understandably elated. Naturally John heads straight to a Beijing's most loved Peking Duck restaurant in the heart of the Hutongs and is fascinated to see and then taste a traditionally inflated and roasted Peking Duck.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E3
programme.desc: Wine enthusiasts Christina and Ed are ready to make their lifelong dream of having a view of a lush green vineyard come true. Their Italian and Chilean roots have led them on a quest to re-locate to wine country.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E5
programme.desc: Dairy, Drugs and Dogs headline in today's visit to Heathrow. On the airfield Airside Ian goes for promotion, whilst inside the terminals Queen of T2 Sue saves a musician from missing his concert and in security there's a serious breach.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E4
programme.desc: Flying into Heathrow: an endangered parrot, and a polar vortex! Whilst Officers Dave and Terry hunt for a wanted man gone missing on a plane, Airside Ian and stickler-for-the-rules Steve battles snow in a blizzard to keep the runways open.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E2
programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. He's there to learn the secret behind their mouthwatering fried chicken, which some say is the best in the south. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E3
programme.desc: Matt meets many, many cows. He learns about, admires and milks South Africa's indigenous Nguni breed in Msinga, Kwa Zulu Natal. Matt meets Xoliswa Ndoyiya (Nelson Mandela's personal chef) to cook the late president's favourite sour milk recipe (umphokoqo) and share memories of her time cooking for an icon.

programme.desc: Puerto Rico is one of the most popular vacation destinations for Americans, and it's easy to see why; everyone speaks English, it's easy to get to, and of course, it's still a part of the US! Host Liesel Hlista starts off her journey with a goal to feel at one with herself and the best way to do that is with a stint of yoga, atop a paddleboard. SUP yoga! Feeling centered, she begins exploring the island by taking a very detailed walking historical tour as well as a food tour. Bouncing around cantinas and trying out slushy drinks made with the local Don Q rum, Liesel gets a unique insight into old San Juan. To step up the action, Liesel also explores all the hands-on activities such as riding horseback on the beach, riding ATV's through the muddy swamps, and hiking through the super lush El Yunque rainforest. Luxurious resorts are only a stone's throw away - hopping islands, Liesel gets to experience the ultra modern and chic El Blok located in Vieques. Between stays at all th.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E5
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, uncovers a hidden life off the busy city of Lijiang where traditional craftsmen, healers, and priest teach him a range of activities from mushroom hunting, and falcon training to deciphering the world's last living hieroglyphic script.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E6
programme.desc: Manu has just one country left before making his final journey back to London, and the finale of his worldwide odyssey. America offers up many amazing food experiences, with Mexican dishes and food trucks, pastrami sandwiches, ribs by a soul food legend, and mouthwatering Italian food. With 30 days and $20,000 to spend, will Manu realize his dream of making it around the world Phileus Fogg-style?

programme.title: United Plates Of America E7
programme.desc: After the Vietnam War ended in 1975, many Vietnamese people migrated to California, much of them settling in San Francisco. In this episode we meet several Vietnamese immigrants, learn about their journey to America and tastes their amazing authentic Vietnamese food.

programme.title: Fish of the Day S3E10
programme.desc: The Poor Knights Islands are the remains of an ancient volcano km off NZ’s North Island East Coast. A place so full of life that at times its difficult to see through the clouds of fish that call this marine reserve home. Clarke learns more about the Islands and a little further offshore catches a marlin that he has always dreamed of catching. A stunning part of NZ, both above and below the water.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E2
programme.desc: Ariana explores the ancient city of Yazd, the bride of the desert, and takes us to a bazaar that sells spices and herbal remedies. Later she visits the oldest and most-renowned pastry shop in the city to introduce the classic dessert that she had as a child, then has a hearty meal with her friend in a restaurant housed in an ancient hammam.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E4
programme.desc: In today's Asian adventure John Torode finds himself in the bustling metropolis of Hong Kong looking for traditional dishes to delight his pallet. John's first stop is the Long Kwai Fong district where he explores the markets with new friend Silvana. Spurred on by the potential for healthy eating, John is taken to an eatery that claims to improve your chances for a long life.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E4
programme.desc: Since childhood Bret and Stephen had big dreams to move to New York City and became Broadway stars. Hard work and dedication to their craft made that dream a reality. Now it's time for this couple to pursue another lifelong dream – to finally find a home overlooking iconic Central Park.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E6
programme.desc: Landing at a hectic Heathrow today is new Border Force Officer Rob investigating job scams, the grass is in desperate need of a trim, and we meet duo Sophie and Rachel who are raving about airside safety.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E5
programme.desc: Dairy, Drugs and Dogs headline in today's visit to Heathrow. On the airfield Airside Ian goes for promotion, whilst inside the terminals Queen of T2 Sue saves a musician from missing his concert and in security there's a serious breach.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E3
programme.desc: Jordan travels to Washington DC for a truly capitol late night experience. He starts his night off on Capitol Hill. Jordan sinks his teeth into a cheesy pimento burger at Eat Bar in Barracks Row, a gastro pub where staffers love to unwind after a long day's work. Then it's off to Blagden Alley for a sweet trip to Hong Kong.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E4
programme.desc: This episode is dedicated to magnificent maize. Matt explores, cooks and eats maize in every shape and form. Guided by fabulous food blogger and pop up restaurateur Khanya Mzongwana he samples maize dishes in bustling taxi ranks and quaint kitchens. He discovers that maize and maize preparation is not only deliciously diverse but also infused with cultural meaning.

programme.title: Lion Kingdom E2
programme.desc: The Glade is a paradise where there is always water, a place where strange things happen. As the dry continues in Ruaha, herds of elephants arrive in the Glade. They dig deep into the sand with their trunks to tap the cleanest waters. The Glade pride copy the elephants - unusual behavior, but not in the Glade. Life carries on in its idiosyncratic way, but soon things may change. Adult male lions are on the horizon, they're following the buffalo. The Njaa pride have already spotted the males. The Njaa are drifters, they consider the buffalo their territory. But even these fearless lionesses will not hunt while the lions are about - and now the males are on their way to the Glade.

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E2
programme.desc: It's springtime, and the Alaska SeaLife Center's hotline is inundated with calls about orphaned harbor seal pups. The team scrambles to stay ahead of the growing list of rescues and rehabs. At the Alaska Raptor Center, a typical day gets flipped upside-down when a call comes in about two bald eagles on the ground. At the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center, it's time to move the wood bison to their spring pasture, but Bull 299 won't make it easy.

programme.title: Search For King Cobra E1
programme.desc: Its 14 feet long with almost 2 teaspoons of available venom. This is the King Cobra. Translated its scientific name means 'snake eater'. A King kills and consumes other snakes up to 10 feet long. All forest residents live in fear of him including human beings. But his empire is under threat? Hes a resident of India the most populated part of the planet, and hes having to mix more and more with villagers. Its March in Indias Western Ghats, and that means one thing for King cobras - finding a mate. Having been dormant for the last few months, they are now fully alert and hot on the trail of female pheromones. The trail leads them right through a crowded village. Enter Gowri Shankar a snake expert who responds to calls from panicked villagers. Instead of beating the snakes to death, Gowri carefully captures them and takes them to a place of safety. Little is known about these highly venomous snakes. Previous research and tagging projects have only started to scratch the surface.

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E3
programme.desc: There's a baby boom in Alaska! The rescue team from the Alaska SeaLife Center hits the road when a newborn sea otter gets separated from its mom. If this baby is alright, she'll require round-the-clock care. A new baby also arrives at the Alaska Raptor Center when a bald eaglet falls from its nest. But there's no time to rest. The team must also jump into action to save a stranded, injured eagle that's lost a fight. And at the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center, two foxes rescued as kits are getting a habitat upgrade. But first they have to learn all the necessary tricks to make the big move.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E2
programme.desc: Zeb Hogan hunts for the fresh water Whipray in the Daily River, northern Australia. The largest one caught so far was 10 feet across and weighed around 800 pounds, with a barb over 12 inches long. He then heads to Thailand on the trail of a giant Stingray, reported to be 600 pounds. These rays are said to grow to the size of small trucks. If true, this would be the largest fresh water fish ever.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E4
programme.desc: Zeb is in Guyana, South America in search of a fish with a terrifying reputation. Wolf fish, known locally as Haimara, are one of the most feared aquatic predators and are said to hunt both animals and humans. Said to be more ferocious than Piranha, Wolf fish can reach 1-meter long and nearly 100 pounds. With minimal info on them, Zeb heads into the Amazon to see if they deserve their reputation.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E3
programme.desc: Streetwise snake-catcher Simon Keys and his sassy herpetologist girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, rush around Snake City to save snakes that have ventured into human territory. They hunt down a frighteningly fast black mamba in a cluttered kitchen, and a Mozambique spitting cobra under a bath that's showering Simon with venom. All before he has to face his irrational fear of heights while trying to retrieve a green mamba from a tree.

programme.title: Stranger Than Nature: Unhinged E3
programme.desc: Beachgoers are stunned and disturbed when a strange alien-like creature washes up on the shores of Montauk, Long Island. Images posted on the internet show the creature with a bird-like beak, a bald body and what appears to a tag tied to its front limb. Millions of people around the world follow the investigation into just what this creature could be. Could it be a mutant from a top-secret government research lab nearby? In the NamiBrand Reserve in Namibia, millions of circles of bare earth surrounded by lush grass dot the earth for miles in all directions. Known as fairy circles, they are an enduring mystery. What is causing the earth to scorch in these perfect patterns? In Australia, ravenous rodents invade farms in the hundreds of thousands. Farmers and their families throw up their hands in despair choosing death over dealing with the mice. What could be causing the mice, which are not even native to the area, from overrunning farms and livelihoods? When 7% of the world's.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: Wild Argentina E1
programme.desc: This episode follows the animals of Argentina, living life at the mercy of the Andean mountains. These peaks dictate a hard existence for every living creature from their summits to the very edge of the Patagonian steppe, forcing even the cutest resident to turn carnivore? Predators stalk the foothills and creepy crawlies lie low in the sandy steppe. Every animal here has a bloodthirsty drive to survive.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E4
programme.desc: Runaways, adventurists, and escape artists-what's gotten into these animals around town? First, Dr. Pol is called in to assess two runaway bulls who've shown up at Tom Knoll's Farm. Across town, Dr. Emily is responding to a complicated emergency calving. It's going to take some repositioning to get this calf out, and Dr. Emily has to hustle in order to save both the calf and mother. Later, at the clinic, Dr. Brenda is helping Miss Kitty who's in with a problem that's making her young owner squirm! Back at their home, Athena and Donar get together and finagle their way out of the house - is there any stopping them? Will Charles ever catch up to these great adventuring Danes? Between canine hijinks, bulls on the loose, and an attempted kitten getaway, the Pol's sure have their hands full!

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S5E4 !
programme.desc: Isn't it bizarre to see animals defy their instinct and form unusual bonds with other species? You will be astonished by watching this episode. A goat doesn't like hanging out with its own kind but enjoys sharing food with a pig. Also a wrestling puppy loves hopping on the back of a pony and pulling off stunts with its best mate.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Brains And Babies E2
programme.desc: If you thought man is the smartest being on the planet, think again. From whales that create bubble walls to catch their fish, to dolphins that work with humans to catch their dinner, to prairie dogs that speak their own language. Don't underestimate these brainiacs or they just might outsmart you through systems of memory, co-operation and even mind control!

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E4
programme.desc: It's midsummer and the state of Alaska is battling uncontrollable wildfires and record-breaking heat. An orphaned sea otter pup narrowly escapes the flames while the rest of the SeaLife Center combats heavy smoke and awaits the arrival of new a puffin hatchling. At the Wildlife Conservation Center, Howie prepares for a once-in-a-lifetime expedition to survey wild wood bison, but the heat is causing complications for their own breeding herd. And at the Alaska Raptor Center, wildfires up north present a problem for a very unique owl.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E3
programme.desc: Zeb heads deep into the Brazilian Amazon in search of an Electric eel large enough to kill a Caiman crocodile. He teams up with a local Amazonian fisherman to track and catch these elusive fish. If it's not too dangerous, Zeb wants to record the biggest electric shock he can without getting electrocuted.

programme.title: Lion Kingdom E3
programme.desc: Change comes to the Glade. An adult male arrives to resume his positions as leader, and father. The cubs grow quickly - there is one male amongst them. When the cub reaches adolescence he begins to play dangerous games, trying to mate with female members of the pride. This will not be tolerated. The leader evicts the young male from the Glade in a short but violent display of authority. The exile's journey into adulthood is fraught with peril. Alone and desperate, hunger drives the teenager to become a scavenger. When he meets another young male exile from the Baobab Pride, his fortunes seem to change. Together they kill their first buffalo and form a bond for life. The young males know the only way they can survive is to follow the buffalo herds. Their journey takes them into the Greater Ruaha River valley, far from their homes. It is here that the Glade male meets a lioness - and that's when the trouble really begins.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E3

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E6
programme.desc: After the death of her mother, Motshidi is starving and alone. In a terrifying reunion with her father, she has everything to lose. A violent traitor rises in the rotten ranks, challenging the selfish princess and bringing an end to Mmamotse's rule. The Makulu Pack make one last stand as the battle for supremacy begins, but with the hyenas gone, it's up to Sega to lead the Matahta Pride to victory.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E1
programme.desc: Mike travels to Austin in search of three of Texas' most amazing fish - one is so smart it can out-think the average fisherman and get away, one is so rare it's found nowhere else on the planet, and the last one is giant and secretive, requiring days of fishing - with little hope of success.

programme.title: Wild 24 S1E1
programme.desc: The Africa savannah crosses 25 countries and is home to millions of animals. Here, herbivores and carnivores are caught in a constant struggle for survival. programme.title: Wild Cats Of India E2
programme.desc: Masters of disguise, India's secretive small cats have lived in the shadow of their larger cousins. In Episode 2 follow wildlife cameraman, Sandesh Kadur, on a quest to uncover the secretive lives of India's Small Cats. This film will explore the incredible intersection where cutting edge camera technology will be complemented by scientific knowledge. Watch, as a family Jungle cats co-exist with a Bengal fox family and follow researchers deep into the realm of the rare clouded leopard.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E2
programme.desc: For animals in the wild, preparing for emergency situations can mean the difference between life and death. From cutting-edge engineering to elaborate escape strategies, follow these creatures of the wild as they prepare for just about anything in some of the World's Weirdest ways.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E4
programme.desc: Runaways, adventurists, and escape artists-what's gotten into these animals around town? First, Dr. Pol is called in to assess two runaway bulls who've shown up at Tom Knoll's Farm. It's going to take some repositioning to get this calf out, and Dr. Emily has to hustle in order to save both the calf and mother. Later, at the clinic, Dr. Brenda is helping Miss Kitty who's in with a problem that's making her young owner squirm! Back at their home, Athena and Donar get together and finagle their way out of the house - is there any stopping them? Will Charles ever catch up to these great adventuring Danes? Between canine hijinks, bulls on the loose, and an attempted kitten getaway, the Pol's sure have their hands full!

He then sets his sights on the Speartooth Shark, which has never had a confirmed sighting in the wild.

programme.desc: Mike's in Taiwan to search for three species of fish. programme.title: Wild 24 S1E2
programme.desc: This film follows animals over 24 hours living in and around one of the driest regions on Earth: the Atacama Desert in northern Chile. Weird rabbit-like rodents, a big cat, hump-less camelids, iconic dancing birds and even penguins battle against the odds in a land of extreme heat and cold.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E2

programme.title: India's Wild Edens

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E4
